<i>noun</i>: 직 [직], 재직 [재ː직], 임용 [이ː묭], 고용 [고용] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>직 [직]</dt><br>
<dd>1. office</dd><br>
<dd>공무원 등이 국가로부터 받은 일정한 직무나 직책.</dd><br>
<dd>A duty or position given to a civil servant, etc., by the government.</dd><br>
<dd>2. job; occupation</dd><br>
<dd>생계를 위하여 일정한 기간 동안 계속하여 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A regular activity done for a specific period of time for one's living.</dd><br>
<dd>3. position</dd><br>
<dd>맡은 직위나 직무.</dd><br>
<dd>One's post or duty.</dd><br>
<dd>4. employment</dd><br>
<dd>직업이나 직위를 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A word used to mean an occupation or position.</dd><br>
<dt>재직 [재ː직]</dt><br>
<dd>employment; service</dd><br>
<dd>직장에 속하여 일하고 있음.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of belonging to and working for an organization.</dd><br>
<dt>임용 [이ː묭]</dt><br>
<dd>appointment; employment; hiring</dd><br>
<dd>직무를 맡기어 사람을 씀.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of hiring someone and assigning a certain job to him/her.</dd><br>
<dt>고용 [고용]</dt><br>
<dd>employment</dd><br>
<dd>돈을 주고 사람에게 일을 시킴.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of paying someone to do work.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>